result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica E Bixenmann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:32 AM Call to Order by Court.  Appearances stated: Defendant Jessica E Bixenmann in court.  Attorney Steven W. Zaleski in court for Jessica E Bixenmann.  Attorney Luke Steiner in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Attorney Zaleski is heard and they are ready to proceed. 
State is heard on agreement. 2 years probation. Defendant to participate in and successfully complete Crawford County Treatment Court. 
Defendant is heard and agrees. 

Court reviews plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form with defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the constitutional and fundamental rights with Defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the elements of the charge with defendant. Defendant states understanding. Court reviews the minimum / maximum penalties with defendant. Defendant states understanding. 

Court asks defendant for plea. Defendant enters a plea of no contest to both count 1 and count 2. Court accepts the defendants pleas and finds that the defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily enters plea. Court finds the defendant guilty of both counts. 

Attorney Steiner is heard on sentencing. 2 years probation. Defendant to participate in and successfully complete Crawford County Treatment Court. Recommends no confinement time.
Attorney Zaleski is heard confirms agreement. 4 days sentence credit.  
Defendant is heard. 

Court supports the recommendations that have been made. Orders Withheld sentence - 2 years probation. Defendant to participate in and successfully complete Crawford County Treatment Court. Participate in any other assessments as deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections and follow through with recommended counseling, treatment or programming. Waive the DNA surcharge for count 2.  Identical sentences. 250.00 Bond to be applied. If probation is revoked 4 days jail credit. Court costs.
